WEBVTT

00:03.583 --> 00:05.574
When I was a little kid,

00:05.583 --> 00:08.074
I used to think ships
were like magic...

00:08.083 --> 00:12.577
sailing in from strange places,
carrying mysterious cargo...

00:12.583 --> 00:16.576
This ship was from
the People's Republic of China,

00:16.583 --> 00:20.075
and the cargo was
kind of special:

00:20.083 --> 00:23.075
a single treasure
literally beyond price.

00:24.625 --> 00:26.081
It'd been on display
during the voyage,

00:26.625 --> 00:29.082
and its security
had been the responsibility

00:29.083 --> 00:31.074
of the Chinese government.

00:31.083 --> 00:35.622
Now it was going to be ours:
Pete Thornton's and mine.

00:39.625 --> 00:41.081
Chu.

00:41.083 --> 00:43.119
I mean,
Commissioner Chu.

00:43.125 --> 00:45.116
Don't be inscrutable
with me, Peter.

00:45.625 --> 00:47.115
It's good to see you again.

00:47.125 --> 00:49.116
And very good to see you

00:49.125 --> 00:50.114
I'd like to introduce

00:50.625 --> 00:52.115
my friend and
colleague, MacGyver.

00:52.125 --> 00:55.617
(speaking Mandarin)

00:56.125 --> 00:57.114
The honor is mine.

00:57.625 --> 00:59.616
You speak Mandarin.

00:59.625 --> 01:01.616
You just heard about 90o/o of it.

01:02.125 --> 01:06.118
May I ask what you do
for the Phoenix organiyation?

01:06.125 --> 01:09.117
Well, MacGyver is a kind
of, uh, troubleshooter.

01:09.125 --> 01:11.662
I trust
we're not expecting trouble.

01:11.667 --> 01:13.658
You know me...
belt and suspenders...

01:13.667 --> 01:15.658
We figured
we'd be better off

01:16.125 --> 01:17.661
a little nervous
than a lot sorry.

01:18.667 --> 01:21.659
Actually, I'm pleased.

01:21.667 --> 01:25.159
Now, if you'll sign the manifest
receiving the item...

01:25.166 --> 01:26.656
Item?

01:26.667 --> 01:28.658
That's some description
for a national treasure,

01:29.166 --> 01:30.155
but, uh, on behalf

01:30.667 --> 01:32.157
of the International
Cultural Exposition...

01:32.667 --> 01:34.157
Uh, maybe...

01:34.166 --> 01:36.157
after we see the dragon?

01:36.166 --> 01:39.158
Troubleshooter and lawyer.

01:39.166 --> 01:41.657
No, just curious
to see a legend.

01:42.166 --> 01:43.155
And you shall.

01:43.709 --> 01:45.165
(speaking Mandarin)

01:49.166 --> 01:53.159
This is the first time it's been
outside of China, isn't it?

01:53.709 --> 01:55.165
That's why I'm being
very careful.

01:59.166 --> 02:00.702
The Ming Dragon.

02:02.166 --> 02:06.205
China is very proud of it
as a work of art...

02:06.208 --> 02:08.199
and part of our history.

02:08.709 --> 02:09.698
It's beautiful.

02:15.709 --> 02:18.200
Hey!

02:18.208 --> 02:19.698
This is a restricted area, Miss.

02:19.709 --> 02:21.199
May I ask
what you're doing here?

02:21.208 --> 02:25.201
Excuse me.
I was invited to a party.

02:26.750 --> 02:27.739
There's no party.

02:28.208 --> 02:30.745
Then let's have one of our own.

